<br>
As far as the force needed to take him out, he Deathtouches every 30 seconds, but hits like a pansy.  Ive done him with a single group and we didnt have a prob keeling him before he 2 deathtouches went off.  This was pre-PoP also.  Bring 2 clerics to be safe and a good damage dealer and you will be golden.  The hardest part about him is finding him up =) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65676"> Injektilo (&gt; ' - ' )&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> &lt;Dark Horizon&gt;<br>
Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaladornus>kaladornus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/25/03 2:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Master Yael</span><hr size=1> Fight was just covered. Send in a gnome or ranger for the DT.<br>
<br>
Also you can pull him solo without Nortlav Assisting (IMPORTANT unless you like having Venril Sathir adding while you are fighting the Keeper of Souls <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   )<br>
<br>
The way down is a big pain in the butt.<br>
<br>
Let me see if I can sum up.<br>
<br>
Go straight through first hallways till you get to a ramp leading to a big building. (12 Elementals, one Golem)<br>
<br>
Hug Left wall till dropoff.<br>
<br>
Keep hugging left wall down a ramp, after a halfpipe-looking area. (Elementals, one Golem, two Flighty Fiends)<br>
<br>
Go through door in Giant Castle, take immediate Left. (Golem and two elementals)<br>
<br>
Take left at T intersection.<br>
<br>
Follow this passage as far down as you can go until you get to a room with fountain on your left. (Three Golems, One Ratman, One Revenant, two Elementals)<br>
<br>
Go straight across this room, do not open any doors, etc.<br>
<br>
Go down a ramp.<br>
<br>
Go through the archway in front of you. (Two elementals)<br>
<br>
Hug RIGHT wall till a fountain.<br>
<br>
Do not go through any doors.<br>
<br>
Straight ahead and around the bend to the left is another archway. <br>
<br>
Go through this archway, hug LEFT wall.<br>
<br>
You will see another archway.<br>
<br>
Go through this archway, hug RIGHT wall. (3-4 Golems, 5-6 Elementals)<br>
<br>
Keep hugging right wall till you see archway on right.<br>
<br>
Do NOT go through archway. (Should be a giant Lake, two elementals, one golem)<br>
<br>
Continue Hugging Right wall till next Archway. (one golem, three elementals)<br>
<br>
Go through archway and stand in fountain. (Two elementals, One Revenant, One Ratman)<br>
<br>
Hug Left wall of Building to the left. Do NOT go in any doors or archways. Walk around the left side of the sloping roof in front of you.<br>
<br>
Broken Gate is on your right. (One Golem, One Elemental)<br>
<br>
Go through Gate until you get to a little pool with Jaeil the Wretched. (One Golem, One Revenant, Two Elementals)<br>
<br>
Continue All the way down till Cavern Opens up. (One Revenant, One Elemental)<br>
<br>
At bottom Turn right and look at Castle in Front of you (One Flighty Fiend, Two Elementals, Ratman)<br>
<br>
Go to Static Revenant standing at bottom. (duh)<br>
<br>
Do NOT go in Castle. Go instead through the Tunnel on your left (3 Golems immediately)<br>
<br>
Follow this passage all the way down to Master Yael. (One Golem, one Ratman, Two Elementals)<br>
<br>
<br>
See, wasn't that easy?<br>
