 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zukobim>Zukobim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/1/03 3:09 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Master Yael</span><hr size=1> Best method to learn the way down is to start a Dwarf rogue and make him worship The Underfoot.<br>
<br>
Play/PL him to level 9 and train the skill as you level.<br>
<br>
You need to get swimming (1), sneak (1) and hide (3) up and you need to prime picklock (6).<br>
Making a macro that does /attack off, /sneak, /hide, attack on helps alot in training the skills in battle.<br>
<br>
Once level and skill is up you can buy a piclock set and travel to paineel (POP books are great for this). <br>
<br>
Run to the hole door and get a bind just outside the door!!<br>
<br>
Picklock the door (its a skill 1 door, so its easy) and swim in.<br>
<br>
Once inside jump out of the water and sneak hide.<br>
<br>
Follow the walls as good as you can and con all mobs.<br>
Mobs that are KOS and see invis can usually be avoided by standing in a corner and not moving while they pass by.<br>
<br>
The advantage of the dwarf rogue over the halfling is that many of the mobs that see invis and are threateningly to the halfling will only be indifferently to the dwarf.<br>
The disadvantage is that you need to level the dwarf abit to get picklock (he can not swim through the hole over the door) and hide and you need to practice them abit to not die too often due to failures.<br>
A halfling starts with 50 in sneak and hide and at level 9 the dwarf can reach the same skill levels. <p><br>
